WEBVTT

00:00:25.250 --> 00:00:32.210
Beyond Journey's End

00:01:29.970 --> 00:01:33.970
29 years after the death of Himmel the Hero,
in the Bier region, located on the Northern Plateau

00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.110
I guess there are cities
on the Northern Plateau.

00:01:43.110 --> 00:01:45.010
There are a lot of bars here.

00:01:45.450 --> 00:01:49.570
This area's the only grain-producing
region on the Northern Plateau.

00:01:49.930 --> 00:01:52.400
It's always had plenty of breweries.

00:01:52.920 --> 00:01:54.670
Huh.

00:01:54.670 --> 00:01:56.800
I was talking to Old Man Fass.

00:01:57.100 --> 00:01:59.600
He said he's almost found Boshaft.

00:02:00.060 --> 00:02:01.420
Really?

00:02:01.420 --> 00:02:04.380
He's been talking about that
since my grandpa was a kid.

00:02:02.260 --> 00:02:04.760
What's Boshaft?

00:02:04.760 --> 00:02:07.230
I've heard about it from Mr. Heiter.

00:02:07.460 --> 00:02:11.870
Long ago, most of the continent was
ruled by a single great empire.

00:02:11.870 --> 00:02:15.530
It was an exquisite liquor
offered to the emperor.

00:02:15.530 --> 00:02:16.740
Huh.

00:02:17.050 --> 00:02:20.630
He would lament about how, because of
Ms. Frieren, he never got to drink it.

00:02:23.700 --> 00:02:25.630
There was a reason for that.

00:02:31.240 --> 00:02:33.700
I don't want to stay here for long.

00:02:33.700 --> 00:02:34.860
Once we're finished shopping—

00:02:34.860 --> 00:02:35.640
Frieren!

00:02:36.360 --> 00:02:38.750
It's you, Frieren!

00:02:41.980 --> 00:02:44.080
I haven't seen you in a century.

00:02:44.080 --> 00:02:46.530
It's been eighty years, Fass.

00:02:46.530 --> 00:02:50.230
You're a stickler for details now?
How unlike you.

00:02:52.200 --> 00:02:54.270
Your roster's changed.

00:02:54.270 --> 00:02:57.620
That young guy who liked
to drink isn't with you?

00:02:57.920 --> 00:02:59.710
Heiter's dead.

00:03:00.290 --> 00:03:01.860
He went peacefully.

00:03:04.160 --> 00:03:07.330
I see. I was too late.

00:03:09.980 --> 00:03:13.730
I've located Boshaft,
the Emperor's Spirits.

00:03:13.730 --> 00:03:15.280
Will you help me?

00:03:15.280 --> 00:03:17.730
You can use magic, right?

00:03:18.430 --> 00:03:21.840
What does magic have to do with Boshaft?

00:03:22.360 --> 00:03:24.030
Come with me, and you'll see.

00:03:31.560 --> 00:03:33.070
It's in here.

00:03:33.070 --> 00:03:36.180
Is this... a mine?

00:03:36.180 --> 00:03:38.930
I dug it all by myself.

00:03:40.710 --> 00:03:45.310
Most people think all dwarves are miners,

00:03:45.830 --> 00:03:48.330
but I grew up in the city.

00:03:48.330 --> 00:03:50.280
I had to study mining from scratch.

00:03:52.080 --> 00:03:55.340
I did it for that legendary liquor.

00:03:56.320 --> 00:03:58.830
Who is this old guy?

00:03:58.830 --> 00:04:01.720
Fass. No one loves liquor as much as him.

00:04:02.220 --> 00:04:06.230
He's spent over two hundred years
looking for Boshaft.

00:04:06.770 --> 00:04:10.090
He asked us for help
the last time we met,

00:04:10.470 --> 00:04:15.350
but we had a Demon King to defeat
at the time, so we said no.

00:04:15.350 --> 00:04:18.360
But Boshaft!

00:04:16.690 --> 00:04:18.360
Let go!

00:04:21.850 --> 00:04:24.950
Pulling Heiter away was no mean feat.

00:04:25.820 --> 00:04:29.670
Why are you digging a mine
to find liquor?

00:04:30.230 --> 00:04:36.380
According to legend, there's Boshaft
stored in the ruins underground here.

00:04:39.050 --> 00:04:41.380
And two hundred years ago,

00:04:41.380 --> 00:04:46.140
when I found this stone monument,
I knew it was true.

00:04:46.830 --> 00:04:48.760
This is ancient elvish.

00:04:49.740 --> 00:04:53.580
The inscription proclaims that Boshaft is
the greatest liquor to have ever existed.

00:04:55.010 --> 00:04:56.270
"Milliarde."

00:04:57.440 --> 00:04:59.990
Perhaps that's who wrote
this inscription.

00:05:01.550 --> 00:05:06.480
You're well-educated if you can
read ancient elvish at your age.

00:05:07.250 --> 00:05:10.990
Ms. Frieren drilled it into me
when I was young.

00:05:11.500 --> 00:05:15.130
Most grimoires are written
in ancient elvish.

00:05:15.130 --> 00:05:17.380
You'll have to learn to read it.

00:05:22.340 --> 00:05:24.410
So it was Milliarde.

00:05:25.760 --> 00:05:31.260
Ever since discovering this inscription,
I've dedicated my life to finding Boshaft.

00:05:31.640 --> 00:05:35.260
And now, it's almost within my grasp.

00:05:35.840 --> 00:05:37.710
You found the ruins?

00:05:38.160 --> 00:05:41.620
The ruins themselves, yes.

00:05:43.330 --> 00:05:47.140
But as you can see, the doors to
this stone chamber won't open.

00:05:47.140 --> 00:05:51.280
A powerful barrier was erected
to preserve the liquor.

00:05:51.590 --> 00:05:54.850
You should be able to break it, though.

00:05:58.260 --> 00:05:59.580
I can't.

00:05:59.580 --> 00:06:01.890
Surely you can.

00:06:01.890 --> 00:06:04.220
It'll take time to remove.

00:06:04.750 --> 00:06:06.930
Those kids wouldn't be happy about that.

00:06:06.930 --> 00:06:09.250
I'll make it worth your while.

00:06:09.690 --> 00:06:10.790
With a grimoire?

00:06:10.790 --> 00:06:14.180
Money! I'll pay you twenty
Reich gold coins.

00:06:16.650 --> 00:06:18.480
That's not even worth considering.

00:06:19.020 --> 00:06:20.690
Please, Frieren!

00:06:20.970 --> 00:06:24.200
It's my dream to drink Boshaft!

00:06:24.200 --> 00:06:26.700
I've been searching for
over two hundred years!

00:06:29.500 --> 00:06:30.700
No.

00:06:34.360 --> 00:06:37.700
Ms. Frieren, perhaps we could help him.

00:06:37.700 --> 00:06:40.840
Yeah. I feel sorry for Old Man Fass.

00:06:41.130 --> 00:06:43.430
What's this about?
You're giving me the creeps.

00:06:43.430 --> 00:06:45.590
Normally, you'd be opposed
to this sort of thing.

00:06:45.590 --> 00:06:49.340
Ms. Frieren, he's offering twenty gold
coins. We can use that on our journey.

00:06:49.340 --> 00:06:50.310
That's a ton of money.

00:06:50.310 --> 00:06:52.730
We won't have to worry about
living expenses for a while.

00:06:52.730 --> 00:06:54.220
What?

00:06:54.220 --> 00:06:57.970
But the barrier will take
three months to remove.

00:06:57.970 --> 00:06:59.310
That's hardly any time at all.

00:06:59.310 --> 00:07:00.230
What?

00:07:01.650 --> 00:07:03.230
We'll do it.

00:07:03.970 --> 00:07:06.350
Don't come crying to me later.

00:07:24.650 --> 00:07:27.170
We're in the final stages
of removing the barrier.

00:07:27.620 --> 00:07:30.130
We should be able to finish tomorrow.

00:07:34.150 --> 00:07:35.670
You don't look very pleased.

00:07:41.140 --> 00:07:42.600
I guess not.

00:07:43.460 --> 00:07:46.520
Boshaft doesn't taste good.

00:07:47.020 --> 00:07:50.060
It's not worth devoting your life to.

00:07:50.060 --> 00:07:52.040
But the inscription said...

00:07:53.950 --> 00:07:59.940
Some elves pass the time
in ways you wouldn't believe.

00:08:13.820 --> 00:08:17.850
Milliarde, you never do anything.
You just gaze off into space.

00:08:18.310 --> 00:08:24.500
Many of our fellow elves spend their
long lives searching for something.

00:08:24.500 --> 00:08:26.060
Why do you think that is?

00:08:26.500 --> 00:08:27.580
Why?

00:08:28.340 --> 00:08:30.850
So that they don't end up like me.

00:08:32.320 --> 00:08:36.640
Frieren, could you imagine the thing
you spent your life searching for

00:08:36.640 --> 00:08:40.330
turning out to be worthless garbage?

00:08:40.820 --> 00:08:43.830
Not at all. What are you talking about?

00:08:44.200 --> 00:08:48.090
My distant past.

00:08:51.910 --> 00:08:55.090
This liquor really is terrible.

00:08:55.610 --> 00:08:57.320
Boshaft.

00:08:57.320 --> 00:09:01.090
That's the awful, cheap liquor
they served at the coronation.

00:09:01.800 --> 00:09:07.110
Before coming to this village,
I carved an inscription to pass the time.

00:09:07.520 --> 00:09:11.260
It says, "Boshaft is the greatest
liquor to have ever existed."

00:09:12.160 --> 00:09:14.230
What was the point of that?

00:09:15.970 --> 00:09:18.170
There was no point at all.

00:09:22.710 --> 00:09:24.350
It's finally time.

00:09:45.290 --> 00:09:47.490
It's well-preserved.

00:09:47.490 --> 00:09:51.490
I never thought I'd get to taste this.

00:09:51.720 --> 00:09:55.140
Let's toast. Drink with me.

00:10:05.770 --> 00:10:07.200
This is...

00:10:11.020 --> 00:10:16.000
Frieren, why did you decline
to search for Boshaft?

00:10:18.590 --> 00:10:21.020
Heiter, you like liquor, right?

00:10:21.020 --> 00:10:22.510
Of course I do.

00:10:22.510 --> 00:10:24.940
Listen to this corrupt priest.

00:10:25.500 --> 00:10:28.780
What would you do if the liquor
you spent your life searching for

00:10:28.780 --> 00:10:31.240
turned out to be unbelievably terrible?

00:10:34.870 --> 00:10:37.430
Well...

00:10:37.910 --> 00:10:39.360
I think I'd laugh it off.

00:10:39.740 --> 00:10:44.230
It tastes bad, right? Then it's
best enjoyed with friends.

00:10:48.870 --> 00:10:50.720
It's so...

00:10:52.830 --> 00:10:54.080
It's terrible.

00:10:54.710 --> 00:10:57.750
It's the worst-tasting drink
I've ever had.

00:11:00.660 --> 00:11:04.080
Why are you just watching? Try it, Stark.

00:11:04.080 --> 00:11:07.190
What? No way. It's terrible, right?

00:11:07.190 --> 00:11:08.690
Just try it.

00:11:12.720 --> 00:11:14.860
It's freaking gross!

00:11:17.860 --> 00:11:20.500
Why is it so gross?

00:11:21.200 --> 00:11:23.150
It really is terrible.

00:11:23.150 --> 00:11:24.140
Try it.

00:11:26.280 --> 00:11:28.200
There's plenty to go around!

00:11:28.200 --> 00:11:30.860
I'll make the whole city suffer with me!

00:11:34.630 --> 00:11:35.870
Frieren.

00:11:35.870 --> 00:11:41.260
My search ended in disappointment,
but I've never had such a fun night.

00:11:41.520 --> 00:11:44.630
I'm glad you guys were here.

00:11:47.210 --> 00:11:50.560
Liquor's meant to be
enjoyed with good times.

00:12:03.020 --> 00:12:06.030
Episode 33: Logistics in the Northern Plateau

00:12:06.030 --> 00:12:10.030
30 years after the death of Himmel the Hero,
in Norm Company territory, located on the Northern Plateau

00:12:12.720 --> 00:12:15.670
Here's your share of bread, Mr. Stark.

00:12:18.970 --> 00:12:23.040
Did you hear that?
This bread just went "clunk."

00:12:23.620 --> 00:12:26.050
That's not a sound food should make.

00:12:26.310 --> 00:12:30.280
We've been eating rock-hard
bread this whole week.

00:12:30.850 --> 00:12:32.800
Don't complain.

00:12:33.370 --> 00:12:38.320
The Northern Plateau is barren outside
of the grain-producing Bier region,

00:12:39.200 --> 00:12:42.100
and goods aren't even circulating now.

00:12:42.670 --> 00:12:46.060
We'll be eating mostly this while
we camp, at the very least.

00:12:47.120 --> 00:12:48.620
That's so sad.

00:12:48.620 --> 00:12:53.520
If we walk another half day,
we should be able to get a decent meal.

00:13:07.210 --> 00:13:09.640
That's an impressive fortress city.

00:13:10.230 --> 00:13:12.540
That's the Norm Company's estate.

00:13:12.540 --> 00:13:14.770
That structure in the center
is their headquarters.

00:13:15.840 --> 00:13:20.320
They deal in various goods,
primarily wheat from the Bier region.

00:13:20.750 --> 00:13:23.580
They're an armed trading company
with the logistics network

00:13:23.580 --> 00:13:28.760
and military force to supply the villages
dotted across the Northern Plateau.

00:13:29.570 --> 00:13:31.690
Not even the state can touch them.

00:13:31.690 --> 00:13:36.080
For all intents and purposes, they rule
humanity on the Northern Plateau.

00:13:36.080 --> 00:13:40.320
But Ms. Frieren, you said earlier
that goods aren't circulating.

00:13:40.870 --> 00:13:42.540
That's the problem.

00:13:42.950 --> 00:13:46.800
I don't know the specific cause,
but things change over time.

00:13:47.410 --> 00:13:51.080
Maybe the Norm Company
isn't as strong as it once was.

00:13:51.940 --> 00:13:57.690
But it's likely that they still have a lot
of influence on the Northern Plateau.

00:13:57.690 --> 00:14:00.400
We should avoid making waves.

00:14:09.090 --> 00:14:10.090
I see.

00:14:10.810 --> 00:14:13.330
So you're Ms. Fern, a first-class mage.

00:14:13.940 --> 00:14:15.590
You may pass.

00:14:17.820 --> 00:14:19.130
That person...

00:14:28.860 --> 00:14:30.490
One moment, please.

00:14:32.240 --> 00:14:33.920
I wonder what's going on.

00:14:40.100 --> 00:14:42.560
I am Norm, the company president.

00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:46.170
Ms. Frieren, mage of the party of heroes,

00:14:46.170 --> 00:14:51.630
you will be paying off the debt
you've owed for eighty years in full.

00:14:52.440 --> 00:14:55.950
Ms. Frieren, you've been carrying debt?

00:14:56.270 --> 00:14:57.470
Just a little.

00:14:57.470 --> 00:14:58.700
Seriously?

00:14:58.700 --> 00:15:01.960
But I was told I could
pay it back anytime.

00:15:02.170 --> 00:15:04.780
That's not what the documents say.

00:15:05.460 --> 00:15:07.760
Verbal agreements are no good.

00:15:07.760 --> 00:15:14.000
It seems my predecessor's predecessor
was lax in that area, but I am not.

00:15:16.160 --> 00:15:22.300
Three Strahl gold, twenty Reich gold,
and various silvers and coppers.

00:15:23.150 --> 00:15:25.720
You're as wealthy as a minor noble.

00:15:25.720 --> 00:15:26.560
Right?

00:15:26.560 --> 00:15:32.320
Your grandfather did us a favor,
so you can keep the change.

00:15:34.540 --> 00:15:35.320
I see.

00:15:37.100 --> 00:15:39.130
This isn't nearly enough.

00:15:41.010 --> 00:15:44.940
Anyway, I have to work in the mines
for three hundred years.

00:15:44.940 --> 00:15:48.080
My journey ends here.

00:15:50.550 --> 00:15:53.840
What are you talking about, Ms. Frieren?

00:15:53.840 --> 00:15:56.590
Why are you dressed like that?
Where's your bag?

00:15:57.030 --> 00:16:00.100
They took everything as collateral.

00:16:17.550 --> 00:16:20.230
Bye, Fern and Stark.

00:16:20.490 --> 00:16:21.740
Take care.

00:16:24.610 --> 00:16:25.750
What?

00:16:26.990 --> 00:16:28.680
What are we going to do?

00:16:29.670 --> 00:16:32.710
All we can do is buy back Ms. Frieren.

00:16:32.710 --> 00:16:34.860
She's not a thing, you know.

00:16:35.380 --> 00:16:39.380
Unfortunately, there's nothing
you can do about it.

00:16:39.670 --> 00:16:40.840
Take a look.

00:16:43.890 --> 00:16:46.370
According to the documents,

00:16:46.370 --> 00:16:48.890
she owes over five hundred Strahl
gold coins including interest.

00:16:48.890 --> 00:16:51.260
Even when converted to Reich gold coins,

00:16:51.260 --> 00:16:54.400
the most trusted currency on the Northern
Plateau, she owes over three hundred.

00:16:54.400 --> 00:16:57.900
Do you think you can procure such a sum?

00:16:58.610 --> 00:17:00.420
No, that would be impossible.

00:17:00.420 --> 00:17:02.370
Seriously, what are we going to do?

00:17:03.050 --> 00:17:05.800
We can't wait three hundred years.

00:17:11.610 --> 00:17:14.910
I don't really like mines.

00:17:14.910 --> 00:17:17.260
They're hot and dusty.

00:17:27.380 --> 00:17:31.400
The president told us
about you, Ms. Frieren.

00:17:33.290 --> 00:17:34.390
I see.

00:17:34.770 --> 00:17:36.730
Shall we get started, then?

00:18:28.390 --> 00:18:30.280
We'll go straight through here.

00:18:31.030 --> 00:18:32.660
You're certain?

00:18:33.210 --> 00:18:35.540
Who do you think I am?

00:18:37.350 --> 00:18:40.730
All right, boys! Start digging!

00:18:40.730 --> 00:18:41.940
Yeah!

00:18:56.390 --> 00:18:58.560
The Norm Company president
of two generations ago

00:18:58.920 --> 00:19:02.580
started out as a backwater noble
cast out to the Northern Plateau.

00:19:03.200 --> 00:19:09.770
He was a great man who invested in this
barren land and built a logistics network,

00:19:09.770 --> 00:19:13.380
bringing stability to people's lives.

00:19:14.900 --> 00:19:19.340
At the time, nobody expected
much from our party of heroes,

00:19:19.340 --> 00:19:22.600
but he provided us with funds
with no repayment deadline.

00:19:25.350 --> 00:19:30.080
I never thought I'd be treated
like this by his grandson.

00:19:31.230 --> 00:19:37.190
But there must be a reason you came
all the way to this mine, right?

00:19:38.450 --> 00:19:42.260
Logistics in the Northern Plateau
are in a terrible state, aren't they?

00:19:42.690 --> 00:19:44.070
I suppose.

00:19:44.070 --> 00:19:48.570
Even my companions complained that
they'd never eaten such hard bread.

00:19:48.570 --> 00:19:51.950
I'm sure they hadn't.
I'm not fond of it either.

00:19:52.970 --> 00:19:55.700
Since conditions have worsened here,

00:19:56.290 --> 00:20:01.960
we've lost a third of our armed
caravans and army fighting demons.

00:20:05.360 --> 00:20:07.970
Our logistics network is in ruins, too.

00:20:08.660 --> 00:20:12.800
If the Norm Company were a nation,
we'd have fallen already.

00:20:17.360 --> 00:20:20.590
However, we are a trading company.

00:20:21.540 --> 00:20:26.180
As long as we have the funds,
we can always rebuild.

00:20:27.540 --> 00:20:32.740
When you arrived in this region, I felt
the Goddess must've brought you here.

00:20:33.490 --> 00:20:39.320
That scrap of paper representing your
party's debt gained tremendous value.

00:20:40.390 --> 00:20:43.570
This mine is still under development.

00:20:43.570 --> 00:20:46.620
If we strike silver ore,
we'll turn a huge profit.

00:20:46.620 --> 00:20:50.740
Enough to forgive the party
of heroes' debt and more.

00:20:52.180 --> 00:20:55.760
It should be easy for you
to find, Ms. Frieren.

00:20:56.320 --> 00:21:01.930
I see. So you're using that
scrap of paper to coerce me.

00:21:02.960 --> 00:21:07.810
If our logistics network falls apart
entirely, many people will starve and die.

00:21:08.260 --> 00:21:13.130
Please save the people of the
Northern Plateau, Ms. Frieren.

00:21:15.880 --> 00:21:18.940
Also, if you help us, you'll
have soft bread to eat

00:21:18.940 --> 00:21:22.960
even in the farthest reaches
of the Northern Plateau.

00:21:23.810 --> 00:21:27.100
You're as shrewd as your grandfather.

00:21:27.500 --> 00:21:30.180
This is why I can't stand merchants.

00:21:30.770 --> 00:21:33.570
Fine. You have a deal.

00:21:34.160 --> 00:21:38.260
Either way, I intended to repay
the debt I owed your grandfather.

00:21:43.280 --> 00:21:47.620
I can't believe we
actually struck silver.

00:21:55.620 --> 00:21:58.200
I'm back. Shall we go?

00:21:58.990 --> 00:22:03.660
Oh, good. We were discussing
how to save you.

00:22:03.660 --> 00:22:06.600
We were planning to raid the mine tonight.

00:22:07.120 --> 00:22:10.150
Sheesh. You're so hot-headed.

00:22:10.820 --> 00:22:15.590
More importantly, from now on,
we'll get to eat soft bread.

00:22:16.380 --> 00:22:19.210
Huh? What does that mean?

00:22:20.980 --> 00:22:25.110
Translation
Sho Stifler
Editing & Typesetting
Geoff Mazzolini
Subtitle Timing
Edgar Cruz
Quality Check
Alicia Ashby
Translation Check
Elizabeth Ellis

00:23:50.070 --> 00:23:52.530
I was worried to death.

00:23:50.620 --> 00:23:52.520
I'll help you bury them.

00:23:51.680 --> 00:23:53.310
Protect the villagers!

00:23:52.550 --> 00:23:54.810
Someone like that can't be saved.

00:23:53.090 --> 00:23:55.410
We were a bit too late.

00:23:53.500 --> 00:23:55.510
Demons destroyed the village...

00:23:54.970 --> 00:23:57.230
There are so few of them.

00:23:55.800 --> 00:23:57.120
Are you praying?

00:23:56.400 --> 00:24:00.020
So Ms. Fern also received
